==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Notornis
<hw>No*tor"nis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>no`tos</grk> the south, or southwest + <?/ bird.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of birds allied to the gallinules, but
having rudimentary wings and incapable of flight. <spn>Notornis
Mantelli</spn> was first known as a fossil bird of New Zealand, but
subsequently a few individuals were found living on the southern island.
It is supposed to be now nearly or quite extinct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nototherium</ent>⟦br⟧
